{"lemma":"بَسِيطٌ","slug":"بَسِيطٌ","root":"ب.س.ط","root_slug":"ب-س-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-س-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2540"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B7%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"wide, extended, spread out"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"easy, simple"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb بَسَطَ (basaṭa, “to extend”). compare Assyrian Neo-Aramaic ܦܫܝܛܐ (pšiṭā) and Hebrew פָּשׁוּט (pashút)."},"ipa":["/ba.siːtˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2540","headword_ar":"بَسِيطَ","root":"bsT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basiyTapN","text_ar":"بَسِيطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaATN","text_ar":"بَسَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa Algayovu basiyTFA mutadaArikFA","text_ar":"وَقَعَ الغَيْثُ بَسِيطًا مُتَدَارِكًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rain fell spreading widely upon the earth, continuously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consecutively."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN basiyTu Aljisomi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بَسِيطُ الجِسْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is tall of body"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basiyTu Alwajohi","text_ar":"بَسِيطُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A man (M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the countenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unwrinkled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bright with joy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busuTN","text_ar":"بُسُطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K. *) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basiyTu Alyadayoni","text_ar":"بَسِيطُ اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extensive, in beneficence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberal, bountiful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busuTN","text_ar":"بُسُطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) [and so]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basiyTu AlbaAEi","text_ar":"بَسِيطُ البَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) [and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAEi","text_ar":"البَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munobasiTu","text_ar":"مُنْبَسِطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaduhu bisoTN","text_ar":"يَدُهُ بِسْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiHonN","text_ar":"طِحْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maToHuwnN","text_ar":"مَطْحُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiTofN","text_ar":"قِطْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoTuwfN","text_ar":"مَقْطُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busuTN","text_ar":"بُسُطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unufN","text_ar":"اُنُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuHN","text_ar":"سُجُحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Z,) and (Z, K) by contraction, (Z,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busoTN","text_ar":"بُسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Z, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mabosuwTapN","text_ar":"مَبْسُوطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His hand is liberal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTolaqapN","text_ar":"مُطْلَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is large in expenditure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in the Kur [v. 69],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balo","text_ar":"بَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadaAhu mabosuwTataAni","text_ar":"يَدَاهُ مَبْسُوطَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and accord. to one reading, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisoTaAni","text_ar":"بِسْطَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and accord. to another, with damm, [as though it were ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busoTaAni","text_ar":"بُسْطَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (Z, K, TA,) [but it is said that] in this case it is used as an inf. n., [and therefore ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busoTaAnN","text_ar":"بُسْطَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for an inf. n. is applied as an epithet to a dual and a pl. subst. without alteration,] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guforAnN","text_ar":"غُفْرانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruDowaAnN","text_ar":"رُضْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, accord. to some, it is most probably [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basoTaAnu","text_ar":"بَسْطَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHomaAnu","text_ar":"رَحْمَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and Talhah Ibn-Musarrif read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisaTaAni","text_ar":"بِسَطَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the meaning is, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nay, his hands are liberal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bountiful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the phrase being a simile; for in this case there is no hand, nor any stretching forth. (TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"limusiYo'i Aln~ahaAri Hat~aY yatuwba","text_ar":"لِمُسِىْءِ النَّهَارِ حَتَّى يَتُوبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadaA A@ll~`hi busoTaAni","text_ar":"يَدَا ا@للّٰهِ بُسْطَانِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAll~ayoli walimusiYo'i All~ayoli Hat~aY yatuwba biAln~ahaAri","text_ar":"بِاللَّيْلِ وَلِمُسِىْءِ اللَّيْلِ حَتَّى يَتُوبَ بِالنَّهَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) or, accord. to one relation, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisoTaAni","text_ar":"بِسْطَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is liberal"},{"kind":"text","text":"in forgiveness"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the evil-doer of the day-time until he repent"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the night, and to the evil-doer of the night-time until he repent in the day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: for a king is said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyadi","text_ar":"اليَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mabosuwTu","text_ar":"مَبْسُوطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when he is (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberal in his gifts"},{"kind":"text","text":"by command and by sign, although he gives nothing thereof with his hand, nor stretches it forth with them at all. (Sgh. TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basiyTN","text_ar":"بَسِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~saAni","text_ar":"اللّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munobasiTu","text_ar":"مُنْبَسِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munobasiTN bilisaAnihi","text_ar":"مُنْبَسِطٌ بِلِسَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) (assumed tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Free,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unconstrained, in tongue, or with his tongue"},{"kind":"text","text":",] applied to a man: (M:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbasiyTu","text_ar":"البَسِيطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of metre of verse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * K;) namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the third; the measure of which consists of musotafoEiluno faAEiluno eight"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a mistake for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four] times:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so called because of the extension of its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaAb","text_ar":"اَسْبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", commencing with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabab","text_ar":"سَبَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"immediately followed by another"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabab","text_ar":"سَبَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is said by Aboo-Is-hák. (M.) ―         -b8-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basiyTN","text_ar":"بَسِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used in philosophy as signifying (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Simple; uncompounded"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["M","K","TA","S","Z","Lth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}